      <h2>Drop and seasonal SMS orchestration</h2>
      <p>SMS launches fail when every subscriber gets the same blast. VIP early access, waitlist confirmations, and back-in-stock alerts need separate consent expectations and frequency caps. Email carries lookbooks and education; SMS carries timing and access.</p>
      <p>Document suppression: recent purchasers, wholesale accounts, open support tickets, and customers who opted into email-only. Run collision checks against Sequenzy email flows before enabling SMS broadcasts.</p>
    </div>

    
    <div class="prose-shopify card mt-8">
      <h2>Extended SMS operations notes</h2>
      <p>Operators in this vertical should review opt-in copy monthly, model cost per delivered message before peak season, and keep a living suppression map shared between SMS and Sequenzy email owners. TCPA exposure from mismatched popup promises exceeds the cost of any single campaign.</p>
      <p>Track opt-out rate by flow, not aggregate list size. A growing SMS list with rising opt-outs is a warning sign — often from duplicate cart reminders or launch texts sent during quiet hours.</p>
    </div>
